area_name: Jello Mold Boulder AKA B Minor Boulder

content.description: Start on gutter closer to "my dog has fleas". First moves are super rad. End on right side of the gutter's bulge (unlike Groovin in B Minor which goes straight up the gutter).
content.location: There are bushes immediately to the right. Check the pictures.

content.description: Funny footwork, stay in the crack, if you're the first one there for the day you'll likely need to clean it out a bit from the bottom before you go up (there's always 1 spiderweb too). Fun to do while waiting for my dog has fleas or shut out.
content.location: Left side closer to West Side Rock. Obvious broken gutter/crack

pathTokens: Jello Mold Boulder AKA B Minor Boulder

content.description: Potentially contains some of the most overlooked boulder problems at sandrock. The quality of the rock itself is better than that of fireplace rock however this rock does collect debris from trees. If you take 2 mins to clean each problem you're good. Walk down off boulder is between West Side Rock and Jello Mold
